{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583013","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583013"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:04:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:04:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1801"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1801","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1801"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.49,0.38,0.1,0,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1801"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79042"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1801","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1801"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1801"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64394"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"136"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1165"},{"type":"tags","id":"1412"},{"type":"tags","id":"3382"},{"type":"tags","id":"3460"},{"type":"tags","id":"4492"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"891"},{"type":"contributions","id":"907"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79042"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old woman presents with a one day history of severe epigastric pain radiating to her back, associated with nausea. She has a history of hypertension, gout and hypertriglyceridaemia. For these she takes perindopril, allopurinol and simvastatin. She is known to consume excessive alcohol on occasion. On examination, her pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 110/70mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, and temperature 38.5C. She is tender in the epigastrium.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her current problem?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alcohol","Gallstones","Hypertriglyceridaemia","Hypercalcaemia","Allopurinol"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient is most likely suffering from acute pancreatitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe causes of pancreatitis can be remembered through the mnemonic \u0022I GET SMASHED\u0022: idiopathic, \u003Cstrong\u003Egallstones\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eethanol\u003C/strong\u003E, trauma, steroids, mumps/malignancy, autoimmune, scorpion sting, \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypertriglycerides\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypercalcaemia\u003C/strong\u003E, ERCP, drugs (hydrochlorothiazide, bactrim, azathioprine and more). The two most common causes are gallstones and alcohol (ethanol), which make up 70% of cases with gallstones causing approximately 40% and alcohol 30% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEven with known alcohol abuse, the presence of gallstones would need to be considered and excluded. This can be done simply and in a non-invasive measure using ultrasound. Additionally, only 10% of people who frequently consume alcohol develop acute pancreatitis, suggesting that there may be a role of additional triggers contributing to the development of pancreatitis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The 2 most common causes of acute pancreatitis are gallstones and alcohol"],"references":["Boxhoorn L, Voermans RP, Bouwense SA, et al. Acute pancreatitis. Lancet .2020;396:726-34 Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32891214/","Bartel, M. Acute Pancreatitis (Internet). MSD Manual. 2020. Available at: https://www.msdmanuals.com/en-au/home/digestive-disorders/pancreatitis/acute-pancreatitis"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64394"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1801"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64394","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64394"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-13T13:47:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T13:47:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1801"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79042"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis